<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100238239648052></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100238239648052><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6456&mid=100238239648052>Agree with last comment</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6456&mid=100238239648052#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=91023><span id= >davisi</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>44 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Oct 6th 11:33 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Personally, I think it's fun to actually role play in an RPG.&nbsp;&nbsp;I mean, that is what it's meant for isn't it?  Personally I agree with the last statment that there shold be more low-level GM events with respective low-level loot.  I have personally noticed that there are not very many quests for us levs 15-20.  I love the thrill of completing quest and seeing the faction and exp changes, AND knowing that I am doing something more to roleplay than just slash and hack.  In fact I just had a good idea if VI would ever do it... that is to offer more experience for quests with worse items.<br><br>But alas, I have gone off subject.  The point is, it sickens me to see people disrespecting the value of ROLEPLAYING in a game that is devoted to ROLEPLAYING.  Btw, who here has actually tried to be in character at all times?  Tough isn't it?  Yes, you'll notice, if you ever try that role playing is actually a challenge if it's done right, but after a while, you actually become your character, and start thinking like they would, almost as if you ARE that character... hence ROLEplaying.<br><br>Sorry about the sour grapes, but this is precisely the reason why Camelot has the potential of being much better than EQ.<br><br>Thanks to all who heed my words, and my you have safe hunting always.<br><br>Annalice, Wizard of the 16th Calling <br>(Tholluxe Paels)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
