	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sorry for the rant guys, just a pet peeve. GMs work hard to come up with events and stuff, and those are one of the things that really kills the motony on EQ.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;   <br>They'd do em a LOT more often if people didn't try to kill em the second they show up. I mean they're GMs. THEY HAVE NO LOOT TABLE. Maybe if ya did manage to bring one down, and not piss em off enough to nuke you to kingdom come, then just maybe you can get some of the items they were carrying, assuming they weren't just spawning it as they gave it to players, which, granted they usually do at the end of events.<br><br>I mean consider, these are NOT mobs folx. These are the people who decide what events to have. They can also make it so that they're unkillable, and/or kill you in about one hit. And they DO fight back occasionally.<br><br>One of my favorite EQ moments was the pixie tag event in gfey about a month back. Wandering through Gfey when a whole bunch of girl pixies showed up and started playing tag. So I played along. One of em ended up falling in love with me, and rooted me so I couldn't run away. lol.<br><br>Then people started trying to kill them.<br><br>Ruined the event. Didn't kill any of the Pixies either. However for a good 3 or 4 hours we had a blast playing tag in gfey. Oh, and for all of you l33t crew who think you can take one of the GMs down, after taking one hit too many from a dumbass high level iksar shammy, one of the pixies charmed him and made him attack the guards. Very short little battle. No GM rez afterward to my knowledge.<br><br>Oh, one last thing. For playing along I got a rokyl's channeling crystal and a mith BP. About 1800pp worth of items in the market at that time. And as I said, the ones trying to kill the GMs got diddly.<br><br>In short, play along when one of these starts, rather than being a jerk. You get more out of the game. And not just financially.<br><br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, the Mad Mage of Povar<